    • Class io.artframework.conf.ArtSettings extends io.artframework.conf.SettingsBase implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • autoTrigger

          boolean autoTrigger
          Set to true if you automatically want to trigger the Actions defined in this ArtContext event if there are no listeners subscribed to this result. Defaults to true.

          As an alternative you can subscribe to this ArtContext by using the ArtContext.onTrigger(Class, TriggerListener) method. Then all actions defined in the config will be executed, unless ArtSettings.executeActions() is false.

          See Also:
          ArtSettings.executeActions()

        • executeActions

          boolean executeActions
          Set to false if you want to prevent the ArtContext from executing any Actions. This only affects actions that would be automatically executed when a Trigger fires and a TriggerListener is attached or ArtSettings.autoTrigger() is set to true. Defaults to true.

          You can always bypass this by directly calling one of the ArtContext methods.

        • autoRegisterAllArt

          boolean autoRegisterAllArt
          If this is set to true, the ART-Framework will automatically scan the whole classpath to find and register any ArtObjects that have a parameterless public constructor.

          Use the ArtProvider methods to register ArtObjects that cannot be constructed so easily.
